  "section_name": "Risk Analysis",
  "text": "Revenue growth volatility represents another key risk factor, with year-over-year growth rates fluctuating significantly across recent quarters. Q1 2025 revenue declined 0.93% year-over-year to $9.626 billion, while Q2 2025 surged 7.22% to $10.321 billion, before moderating to just 0.91% growth in Q3 2025 at $10.415 billion. This inconsistency suggests sensitivity to macroeconomic conditions and consumer spending patterns, which could pressure future performance if economic headwinds intensify. Net income growth has similarly varied, ranging from 0.59% in Q3 2025 to 11.65% in Q2 2025, indicating potential earnings volatility that may concern investors seeking predictable returns.",
